This repository contains PATCHES and BUILD SCRIPTS for the NVIDIA 418.113 driver.
It does NOT contain the NVIDIA driver source code or binaries.

The NVIDIA driver is proprietary software licensed under the NVIDIA End User License Agreement (EULA).
You must download the official driver from NVIDIA's website:
https://www.nvidia.com/Download/index.aspx

This repository only provides:
- Patch files (.patch) to fix kernel 7.x compatibility
- Build scripts to apply patches and compile the driver
- Documentation on the patching process

To use this repository:
1. Download NVIDIA-Linux-x86_64-418.113.run from NVIDIA's official site
2. Place it in /opt/nvidia/ (or update the build script path)
3. Run the build script to extract, patch, and compile

The patches are derivative works created for interoperability purposes.
They are provided under MIT License for the patch files themselves.